										<p id="BlogTitle">An Alternative Way to Help Antiwar.com</p>
					<p id="BlogDate">Posted By <u>Angela Keaton</u> On November 27, 2012 @ 6:18 pm In <u>News</u> | <u><a href='#comments_controls'>Comments Disabled</a></u></p>
					<div id="BlogContent"><p>You have asked for it.  Now you have it.  Antiwar.com is accepting Bitcoin.  &#8220;<a href="https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Main_Page" rel="external">Bitcoin is a peer-to-peer currency</a> <sup>[1]</sup>. Peer-to-peer means that no central authority issues new money or tracks transactions. These tasks are managed collectively by the network.&#8221; </p>
<p>Our public donation address is: 1M87hiTAa49enJKVeT9gzLjYmJoYh9V98.   Our short address is: https://btc.to/8a1. For those of you with smart phones, the QR code is embedded below. </p>
<p><a href="http://www.antiwar.com/coinbase/antiwar.png" target="_blank"><br />
<br />
</a></p>
<p>UPDATE:  What a difference a year makes? We have been working with crypto currency ever since, <a href="https://coinbase.com/?r=503c2bf8209b4d00020001c2" rel="external">using CoinBase.com</a> <sup>[2]</sup> as a processor.  Also, the forward thinking BitPay has been a great way to Cash out for non profits free of charge. In addition, we now take Litecoin at LZfkKsz5obysHYCcxCMQHGdize5gisVveV.  Please visit <a href="http://www.bitcoinnotbombs.com/" rel="external">Bitcoin Not Bombs</a> <sup>[3]</sup> for more about crypto currency and peace economies. </p>
